Package au.edu.anu.rscs.aot.collections

Class QuickListOfLists<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • au.edu.anu.rscs.aot.collections.QuickListOfLists<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the list content type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Sizeable, Textable, java.lang.Iterable<T>, java.util.Collection<T>
    public class QuickListOfLists<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Collection<T>, Textable, Sizeable

    An immutable list of lists enabling to iterate over the whole set as if it was a single list, with a minimal cost at creation time (hence the 'Quick'). Immutable, but the elementary lists added to this one may not be immutable.

    CAUTION: the contained lists may have changed between two accesses to this one - so use with care!

    Inherited methods toArray() and containsAll(...) are not supported and will throw an UnsupportedOperationException.

    Author:
    Jacques Gignoux - 4/6/2012
